197 // Debug Printing Into TTY

207 // Debug Logging for ShowDebugLogWindow(). This is designed for relatively rare events so please don't spam.
208 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(...) ImGui::DebugLog(__VA_ARGS__)
209 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_ACTIVEID(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventActiveId) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
210 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_FOCUS(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventFocus) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
211 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_POPUP(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventPopup) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
212 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_NAV(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventNav) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
213 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_CLIPPER(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventClipper) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
214 #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_IO(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventIO) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)

219 // "Paranoid" Debug Asserts are meant to only be enabled during specific debugging/work, otherwise would slow down the code too much.
220 // We currently don't have many of those so the effect is currently negligible, but onward intent to add more aggressive ones in the code.

244 #define IM_MEMALIGN(_OFF,_ALIGN) (((_OFF) + ((_ALIGN) - 1)) & ~((_ALIGN) - 1)) // Memory align e.g. IM_ALIGN(0,4)=0, IM_ALIGN(1,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(4,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(5,4)=8
245 #define IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(_VAL) ((int)((_VAL) * 255.0f + ((_VAL)>=0 ? 0.5f : -0.5f))) // Unsaturated, for display purpose

264 // Debug Tools
265 // Use 'Metrics/Debugger->Tools->Item Picker' to break into the call-stack of a specific item.
266 // This will call IM_DEBUG_BREAK() which you may redefine yourself. See https://github.com/scottt/debugbreak for more reference.
267 #ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK
268 #if defined (_MSC_VER)
269 #define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __debugbreak()
270 #elif defined(__clang__)
271 #define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __builtin_debugtrap()
272 #elif defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__))
273 #define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile("int $0x03")
274 #elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__thumb__)
275 #define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xde01")
276 #elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
277 #define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xe7f001f0");
278 #else
279 #define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() IM_ASSERT(0) // It is expected that you define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() into something that will break nicely in a debugger!
280 #endif
281 #endif // #ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK

319 // Helpers: Bit manipulation
320 static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(int v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
321 static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(ImU64 v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
322 static inline int ImUpperPowerOfTwo(int v) { v--; v |= v >> 1; v |= v >> 2; v |= v >> 4; v |= v >> 8; v |= v >> 16; v++; return v; }

363 // Helpers: ImVec2/ImVec4 operators
364 // We are keeping those disabled by default so they don't leak in user space, to allow user enabling implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and their own types (using IM_VEC2_CLASS_EXTRA etc.)
365 // We unfortunately don't have a unary- operator for ImVec2 because this would needs to be defined inside the class itself.
366 #ifdef IMGUI_DEFINE_MATH_OPERATORS
367 IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
368 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs, lhs.y * rhs); }
369 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs, lhs.y / rhs); }
370 static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y); }
371 static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y); }
372 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
373 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs.x, lhs.y / rhs.y); }
374 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
375 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
376 static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
377 static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
378 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs.x; lhs.y *= rhs.y; return lhs; }
379 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs.x; lhs.y /= rhs.y; return lhs; }
380 static inline ImVec4 operator+(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y, lhs.z + rhs.z, lhs.w + rhs.w); }
381 static inline ImVec4 operator-(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y, lhs.z - rhs.z, lhs.w - rhs.w); }
382 static inline ImVec4 operator*(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y, lhs.z * rhs.z, lhs.w * rhs.w); }
383 IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE
384 #endif

422 static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImPow with either float/double and need the precision
423 static inline double ImPow(double x, double y) { return pow(x, y); }
424 static inline float ImLog(float x) { return logf(x); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImLog with either float/double and need the precision
425 static inline double ImLog(double x) { return log(x); }
426 static inline int ImAbs(int x) { return x < 0 ? -x : x; }
427 static inline float ImAbs(float x) { return fabsf(x); }
428 static inline double ImAbs(double x) { return fabs(x); }
429 static inline float ImSign(float x) { return (x < 0.0f) ? -1.0f : (x > 0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f; } // Sign operator - returns -1, 0 or 1 based on sign of argument
430 static inline double ImSign(double x) { return (x < 0.0) ? -1.0 : (x > 0.0) ? 1.0 : 0.0; }
431 #ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_SSE

433 #else
434 static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return 1.0f / sqrtf(x); }
435 #endif
436 static inline double ImRsqrt(double x) { return 1.0 / sqrt(x); }
437 #endif
438 // - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
439 // (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
440 template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
441 template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
442 template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
443 template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
444 template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
445 template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
446 template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
447 // - Misc maths helpers
448 static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
449 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
450 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
451 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
452 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
453 static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
454 static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
455 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); }
456 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y) + (lhs.z * lhs.z) + (lhs.w * lhs.w); }
457 static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return ImRsqrt(d); return fail_value; }
458 static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }
459 static inline float ImFloorSigned(float f) { return (float)((f >= 0 || (float)(int)f == f) ? (int)f : (int)f - 1); } // Decent replacement for floorf()
460 static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)(v.x), (float)(int)(v.y)); }
461 static inline ImVec2 ImFloorSigned(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2(ImFloorSigned(v.x), ImFloorSigned(v.y)); }
462 static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
463 static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
464 static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
465 static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
466 static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
467 static inline bool ImIsFloatAboveGuaranteedIntegerPrecision(float f) { return f <= -16777216 || f >= 16777216; }

501 // Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
502 // NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
503 struct IMGUI_API ImRect
504 {
505  ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
506  ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
507 
508  constexpr ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
509  constexpr ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
510  constexpr ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
511  constexpr ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
512 
513  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
514  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
515  float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
516  float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
517  float GetArea() const { return (Max.x - Min.x) * (Max.y - Min.y); }
518  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
519  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
520  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
521  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
522  bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
523  bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
524  bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
525  void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
526  void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
527  void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
528  void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
529  void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
530  void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
531  void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
532  void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
533  void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
534  void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
535  bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
536  ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
537 };

540 // Helper: ImBitArray
541 inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
542 inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
543 inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
544 inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2) // Works on range [n..n2)
545 {
546  n2--;
547  while (n <= n2)
548  {
549  int a_mod = (n & 31);
550  int b_mod = (n2 > (n | 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
551  ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
552  arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
553  n = (n + 32) & ~31;
554  }
555 }
556 
557 // Helper: ImBitArray class (wrapper over ImBitArray functions)
558 // Store 1-bit per value.
559 template<int BITCOUNT, int OFFSET = 0>
560 struct ImBitArray
561 {
562  ImU32 Storage[(BITCOUNT + 31) >> 5];
563  ImBitArray() { ClearAllBits(); }
564  void ClearAllBits() { memset(Storage, 0, sizeof(Storage)); }
565  void SetAllBits() { memset(Storage, 255, sizeof(Storage)); }
566  bool TestBit(int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
567  void SetBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage, n); }
568  void ClearBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage, n); }
569  void SetBitRange(int n, int n2) { n += OFFSET; n2 += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT && n2 > n && n2 <= BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBitRange(Storage, n, n2); } // Works on range [n..n2)
570  bool operator[](int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
571 };
572 
573 // Helper: ImBitVector
574 // Store 1-bit per value.
575 struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
576 {
577  ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
578  void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
579  void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
580  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
581  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
582  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
583 };

585 // Helper: ImSpan<>
586 // Pointing to a span of data we don't own.
587 template<typename T>
588 struct ImSpan
589 {
590  T* Data;
591  T* DataEnd;
592 
593  // Constructors, destructor
594  inline ImSpan() { Data = DataEnd = NULL; }
595  inline ImSpan(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
596  inline ImSpan(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
597 
598  inline void set(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
599  inline void set(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
600  inline int size() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data); }
601  inline int size_in_bytes() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data) * (int)sizeof(T); }
602  inline T& operator[](int i) { T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
603  inline const T& operator[](int i) const { const T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
604 
605  inline T* begin() { return Data; }
606  inline const T* begin() const { return Data; }
607  inline T* end() { return DataEnd; }
608  inline const T* end() const { return DataEnd; }
609 
610  // Utilities
611  inline int index_from_ptr(const T* it) const { IM_ASSERT(it >= Data && it < DataEnd); const ptrdiff_t off = it - Data; return (int)off; }
612 };
613 
614 // Helper: ImSpanAllocator<>
615 // Facilitate storing multiple chunks into a single large block (the "arena")
616 // - Usage: call Reserve() N times, allocate GetArenaSizeInBytes() worth, pass it to SetArenaBasePtr(), call GetSpan() N times to retrieve the aligned ranges.
617 template<int CHUNKS>
618 struct ImSpanAllocator
619 {
620  char* BasePtr;
621  int CurrOff;
622  int CurrIdx;
623  int Offsets[CHUNKS];
624  int Sizes[CHUNKS];
625 
626  ImSpanAllocator() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
627  inline void Reserve(int n, size_t sz, int a=4) { IM_ASSERT(n == CurrIdx && n < CHUNKS); CurrOff = IM_MEMALIGN(CurrOff, a); Offsets[n] = CurrOff; Sizes[n] = (int)sz; CurrIdx++; CurrOff += (int)sz; }
628  inline int GetArenaSizeInBytes() { return CurrOff; }
629  inline void SetArenaBasePtr(void* base_ptr) { BasePtr = (char*)base_ptr; }
630  inline void* GetSpanPtrBegin(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n]); }
631  inline void* GetSpanPtrEnd(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n] + Sizes[n]); }
632  template<typename T>
633  inline void GetSpan(int n, ImSpan<T>* span) { span->set((T*)GetSpanPtrBegin(n), (T*)GetSpanPtrEnd(n)); }
634 };
635 
636 // Helper: ImPool<>
637 // Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
638 // Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
639 typedef int ImPoolIdx;
640 template<typename T>
641 struct ImPool
642 {
643  ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
644  ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
645  ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
646  ImPoolIdx AliveCount; // Number of active/alive items (for display purpose)
647 
648  ImPool() { FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
649  ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
650  T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
651  T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
652  ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
653  T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
654  bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
655  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
656  T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); AliveCount++; return &Buf[idx]; }
657  void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
658  void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); AliveCount--; }
659  void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
660 
661  // To iterate a ImPool: for (int n = 0; n < pool.GetMapSize(); n++) if (T* t = pool.TryGetMapData(n)) { ... }
662  // Can be avoided if you know .Remove() has never been called on the pool, or AliveCount == GetMapSize()
663  int GetAliveCount() const { return AliveCount; } // Number of active/alive items in the pool (for display purpose)
664  int GetBufSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
665  int GetMapSize() const { return Map.Data.Size; } // It is the map we need iterate to find valid items, since we don't have "alive" storage anywhere
666  T* TryGetMapData(ImPoolIdx n) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx == -1) return NULL; return GetByIndex(idx); }
667 #ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS
668  int GetSize() { return GetMapSize(); } // For ImPlot: should use GetMapSize() from (IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18304)
669 #endif
670 };
671 
672 // Helper: ImChunkStream<>
673 // Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
674 // This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
675 // We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries.
676 // The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
677 template<typename T>
678 struct ImChunkStream
679 {
680  ImVector<char> Buf;
681 
682  void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
683  bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
684  int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
685  T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = IM_MEMALIGN(HDR_SZ + sz, 4u); int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
686  T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
687  T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
688  int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
689  T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
690  int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
691  T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
692  void swap(ImChunkStream<T>& rhs) { rhs.Buf.swap(Buf); }
693 
694 };
695 
696 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
697 // [SECTION] ImDrawList support
698 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
699 
700 // ImDrawList: Helper function to calculate a circle's segment count given its radius and a "maximum error" value.
701 // Estimation of number of circle segment based on error is derived using method described in https://stackoverflow.com/a/2244088/15194693
702 // Number of segments (N) is calculated using equation:
703 // N = ceil ( pi / acos(1 - error / r) ) where r > 0, error <= r
704 // Our equation is significantly simpler that one in the post thanks for choosing segment that is
705 // perpendicular to X axis. Follow steps in the article from this starting condition and you will
706 // will get this result.
707 //
708 // Rendering circles with an odd number of segments, while mathematically correct will produce
709 // asymmetrical results on the raster grid. Therefore we're rounding N to next even number (7->8, 8->8, 9->10 etc.)
710 #define IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN(_V) ((((_V) + 1) / 2) * 2)
711 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN 4
712 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX 512
713 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC(_RAD,_MAXERROR) ImClamp(IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN((int)ImCeil(IM_PI / ImAcos(1 - ImMin((_MAXERROR), (_RAD)) / (_RAD)))), IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN, IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX)
714 
715 // Raw equation from IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC rewritten for 'r' and 'error'.
716 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_R(_N,_MAXERROR) ((_MAXERROR) / (1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))))
717 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_ERROR(_N,_RAD) ((1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))) / (_RAD))
718 
719 // ImDrawList: Lookup table size for adaptive arc drawing, cover full circle.
720 #ifndef IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE
721 #define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE 48 // Number of samples in lookup table.
722 #endif
723 #define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_SAMPLE_MAX IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE // Sample index _PathArcToFastEx() for 360 angle.
724 
725 // Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
726 // You may want to create your own instance of this if you want to use ImDrawList completely without ImGui. In that case, watch out for future changes to this structure.
727 struct IMGUI_API ImDrawListSharedData
728 {
729  ImVec2 TexUvWhitePixel; // UV of white pixel in the atlas
730  ImFont* Font; // Current/default font (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
731  float FontSize; // Current/default font size (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
732  float CurveTessellationTol; // Tessellation tolerance when using PathBezierCurveTo()
733  float CircleSegmentMaxError; // Number of circle segments to use per pixel of radius for AddCircle() etc
734  ImVec4 ClipRectFullscreen; // Value for PushClipRectFullscreen()
735  ImDrawListFlags InitialFlags; // Initial flags at the beginning of the frame (it is possible to alter flags on a per-drawlist basis afterwards)
736 
737  // [Internal] Temp write buffer
738  ImVector<ImVec2> TempBuffer;
739 
740  // [Internal] Lookup tables
741  ImVec2 ArcFastVtx[IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE]; // Sample points on the quarter of the circle.
742  float ArcFastRadiusCutoff; // Cutoff radius after which arc drawing will fallback to slower PathArcTo()
743  ImU8 CircleSegmentCounts[64]; // Precomputed segment count for given radius before we calculate it dynamically (to avoid calculation overhead)
744  const ImVec4* TexUvLines; // UV of anti-aliased lines in the atlas
745 
746  ImDrawListSharedData();
747  void SetCircleTessellationMaxError(float max_error);
748 };

1019 // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
1020 // For a given item ID, access with ImGui::GetInputTextState()
1021 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
1022 {
1023  ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
1024  int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 length is valid even if TextA is not.
1025  ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
1026  ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
1027  ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
1028  bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
1029  int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
1030  float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
1031  ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
1032  float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
1033  bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
1034  bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
1035  bool Edited; // edited this frame
1036  ImGuiInputTextFlags Flags; // copy of InputText() flags. may be used to check if e.g. ImGuiInputTextFlags_Password is set.
1037 
1038  ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1039  void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
1040  void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
1041  int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
1042  int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
1043  void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
1044 
1045  // Cursor & Selection
1046  void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
1047  void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
1048  bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
1049  void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
1050  int GetCursorPos() const { return Stb.cursor; }
1051  int GetSelectionStart() const { return Stb.select_start; }
1052  int GetSelectionEnd() const { return Stb.select_end; }
1053  void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
1054 };

1316  ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterX = 1 << 2, // If item is not visible: scroll to make the item centered on X axis [rarely used]

1318  ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterX = 1 << 4, // Always center the result item on X axis [rarely used]
1319  ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterY = 1 << 5, // Always center the result item on Y axis [default for Y axis for appearing window)
1320  ImGuiScrollFlags_NoScrollParent = 1 << 6, // Disable forwarding scrolling to parent window if required to keep item/rect visible (only scroll window the function was applied to).
1321  ImGuiScrollFlags_MaskX_ = ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleEdgeX | ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterX | ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterX,

1446 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1447 // [SECTION] Viewport support
1448 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1449 
1450 // ImGuiViewport Private/Internals fields (cardinal sin: we are using inheritance!)
1451 // Every instance of ImGuiViewport is in fact a ImGuiViewportP.
1452 struct ImGuiViewportP : public ImGuiViewport
1453 {
1454  int DrawListsLastFrame[2]; // Last frame number the background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists were used
1455  ImDrawList* DrawLists[2]; // Convenience background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists. We use them to draw software mouser cursor when io.MouseDrawCursor is set and to draw most debug overlays.
1456  ImDrawData DrawDataP;
1457  ImDrawDataBuilder DrawDataBuilder;
1458 
1459  ImVec2 WorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset from Pos to top-left corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,+main_menu_bar_height). Work Area is Full Area but without menu-bars/status-bars (so WorkArea always fit inside Pos/Size!)
1460  ImVec2 WorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset from Pos+Size to bottom-right corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,-status_bar_height).
1461  ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally >= 0.0f.
1462  ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally <= 0.0f.
1463 
1464  ImGuiViewportP() { DrawListsLastFrame[0] = DrawListsLastFrame[1] = -1; DrawLists[0] = DrawLists[1] = NULL; }
1465  ~ImGuiViewportP() { if (DrawLists[0]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[0]); if (DrawLists[1]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[1]); }
1466 
1467  // Calculate work rect pos/size given a set of offset (we have 1 pair of offset for rect locked from last frame data, and 1 pair for currently building rect)
1468  ImVec2 CalcWorkRectPos(const ImVec2& off_min) const { return ImVec2(Pos.x + off_min.x, Pos.y + off_min.y); }
1469  ImVec2 CalcWorkRectSize(const ImVec2& off_min, const ImVec2& off_max) const { return ImVec2(ImMax(0.0f, Size.x - off_min.x + off_max.x), ImMax(0.0f, Size.y - off_min.y + off_max.y)); }
1470  void UpdateWorkRect() { WorkPos = CalcWorkRectPos(WorkOffsetMin); WorkSize = CalcWorkRectSize(WorkOffsetMin, WorkOffsetMax); } // Update public fields
1471 
1472  // Helpers to retrieve ImRect (we don't need to store BuildWorkRect as every access tend to change it, hence the code asymmetry)
1473  ImRect GetMainRect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1474  ImRect GetWorkRect() const { return ImRect(WorkPos.x, WorkPos.y, WorkPos.x + WorkSize.x, WorkPos.y + WorkSize.y); }
1475  ImRect GetBuildWorkRect() const { ImVec2 pos = CalcWorkRectPos(BuildWorkOffsetMin); ImVec2 size = CalcWorkRectSize(BuildWorkOffsetMin, BuildWorkOffsetMax); return ImRect(pos.x, pos.y, pos.x + size.x, pos.y + size.y); }
1476 };

2027 // Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.
2028 // (That's theory, in practice the delimitation between ImGuiWindow and ImGuiWindowTempData is quite tenuous and could be reconsidered..)
2029 // (This doesn't need a constructor because we zero-clear it as part of ImGuiWindow and all frame-temporary data are setup on Begin)
2030 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
2031 {
2032  // Layout
2033  ImVec2 CursorPos; // Current emitting position, in absolute coordinates.
2034  ImVec2 CursorPosPrevLine;
2035  ImVec2 CursorStartPos; // Initial position after Begin(), generally ~ window position + WindowPadding.
2036  ImVec2 CursorMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSize at the beginning of next frame, for scrolling range and auto-resize. Always growing during the frame.
2037  ImVec2 IdealMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSizeIdeal at the beginning of next frame, for auto-resize only. Always growing during the frame.
2038  ImVec2 CurrLineSize;
2039  ImVec2 PrevLineSize;
2040  float CurrLineTextBaseOffset; // Baseline offset (0.0f by default on a new line, generally == style.FramePadding.y when a framed item has been added).
2041  float PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
2042  bool IsSameLine;
2043  bool IsSetPos;
2044  ImVec1 Indent; // Indentation / start position from left of window (increased by TreePush/TreePop, etc.)
2045  ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
2046  ImVec1 GroupOffset;
2047  ImVec2 CursorStartPosLossyness;// Record the loss of precision of CursorStartPos due to really large scrolling amount. This is used by clipper to compensentate and fix the most common use case of large scroll area.
2048 
2049  // Keyboard/Gamepad navigation
2050  ImGuiNavLayer NavLayerCurrent; // Current layer, 0..31 (we currently only use 0..1)
2051  short NavLayersActiveMask; // Which layers have been written to (result from previous frame)
2052  short NavLayersActiveMaskNext;// Which layers have been written to (accumulator for current frame)
2053  ImGuiID NavFocusScopeIdCurrent; // Current focus scope ID while appending
2054  bool NavHideHighlightOneFrame;
2055  bool NavHasScroll; // Set when scrolling can be used (ScrollMax > 0.0f)
2056 
2057  // Miscellaneous
2058  bool MenuBarAppending; // FIXME: Remove this
2059  ImVec2 MenuBarOffset; // MenuBarOffset.x is sort of equivalent of a per-layer CursorPos.x, saved/restored as we switch to the menu bar. The only situation when MenuBarOffset.y is > 0 if when (SafeAreaPadding.y > FramePadding.y), often used on TVs.
2060  ImGuiMenuColumns MenuColumns; // Simplified columns storage for menu items measurement
2061  int TreeDepth; // Current tree depth.
2062  ImU32 TreeJumpToParentOnPopMask; // Store a copy of !g.NavIdIsAlive for TreeDepth 0..31.. Could be turned into a ImU64 if necessary.
2063  ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> ChildWindows;
2064  ImGuiStorage* StateStorage; // Current persistent per-window storage (store e.g. tree node open/close state)
2065  ImGuiOldColumns* CurrentColumns; // Current columns set
2066  int CurrentTableIdx; // Current table index (into g.Tables)
2067  ImGuiLayoutType LayoutType;
2068  ImGuiLayoutType ParentLayoutType; // Layout type of parent window at the time of Begin()
2069 
2070  // Local parameters stacks
2071  // We store the current settings outside of the vectors to increase memory locality (reduce cache misses). The vectors are rarely modified. Also it allows us to not heap allocate for short-lived windows which are not using those settings.
2072  float ItemWidth; // Current item width (>0.0: width in pixels, <0.0: align xx pixels to the right of window).
2073  float TextWrapPos; // Current text wrap pos.
2074  ImVector<float> ItemWidthStack; // Store item widths to restore (attention: .back() is not == ItemWidth)
2075  ImVector<float> TextWrapPosStack; // Store text wrap pos to restore (attention: .back() is not == TextWrapPos)
2076 };

2078 // Storage for one window
2079 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindow
2080 {

2082  ImGuiID ID; // == ImHashStr(Name)
2083  ImGuiWindowFlags Flags; // See enum ImGuiWindowFlags_
2084  ImGuiViewportP* Viewport; // Always set in Begin(). Inactive windows may have a NULL value here if their viewport was discarded.
2085  ImVec2 Pos; // Position (always rounded-up to nearest pixel)

2091  ImVec2 WindowPadding; // Window padding at the time of Begin().

2093  float WindowBorderSize; // Window border size at the time of Begin().
2094  int NameBufLen; // Size of buffer storing Name. May be larger than strlen(Name)!
2095  ImGuiID MoveId; // == window->GetID("#MOVE")
2096  ImGuiID ChildId; // ID of corresponding item in parent window (for navigation to return from child window to parent window)
2097  ImVec2 Scroll;
2098  ImVec2 ScrollMax;
2099  ImVec2 ScrollTarget; // target scroll position. stored as cursor position with scrolling canceled out, so the highest point is always 0.0f. (FLT_MAX for no change)
2100  ImVec2 ScrollTargetCenterRatio; // 0.0f = scroll so that target position is at top, 0.5f = scroll so that target position is centered
2101  ImVec2 ScrollTargetEdgeSnapDist; // 0.0f = no snapping, >0.0f snapping threshold
2102  ImVec2 ScrollbarSizes; // Size taken by each scrollbars on their smaller axis. Pay attention! ScrollbarSizes.x == width of the vertical scrollbar, ScrollbarSizes.y = height of the horizontal scrollbar.
2103  bool ScrollbarX, ScrollbarY; // Are scrollbars visible?
2104  bool Active; // Set to true on Begin(), unless Collapsed
2105  bool WasActive;
2106  bool WriteAccessed; // Set to true when any widget access the current window
2107  bool Collapsed; // Set when collapsing window to become only title-bar
2108  bool WantCollapseToggle;
2109  bool SkipItems; // Set when items can safely be all clipped (e.g. window not visible or collapsed)
2110  bool Appearing; // Set during the frame where the window is appearing (or re-appearing)
2111  bool Hidden; // Do not display (== HiddenFrames*** > 0)
2112  bool IsFallbackWindow; // Set on the "Debug##Default" window.
2113  bool IsExplicitChild; // Set when passed _ChildWindow, left to false by BeginDocked()
2114  bool HasCloseButton; // Set when the window has a close button (p_open != NULL)
2115  signed char ResizeBorderHeld; // Current border being held for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
2116  short BeginCount; // Number of Begin() during the current frame (generally 0 or 1, 1+ if appending via multiple Begin/End pairs)
2117  short BeginCountPreviousFrame; // Number of Begin() during the previous frame
2118  short BeginOrderWithinParent; // Begin() order within immediate parent window, if we are a child window. Otherwise 0.
2119  short BeginOrderWithinContext; // Begin() order within entire imgui context. This is mostly used for debugging submission order related issues.
2120  short FocusOrder; // Order within WindowsFocusOrder[], altered when windows are focused.
2121  ImGuiID PopupId; // ID in the popup stack when this window is used as a popup/menu (because we use generic Name/ID for recycling)
2122  ImS8 AutoFitFramesX, AutoFitFramesY;
2123  ImS8 AutoFitChildAxises;
2124  bool AutoFitOnlyGrows;
2125  ImGuiDir AutoPosLastDirection;
2126  ImS8 HiddenFramesCanSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames
2127  ImS8 HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames while allowing items to be submitted so we can measure their size
2128  ImS8 HiddenFramesForRenderOnly; // Hide the window until frame N at Render() time only
2129  ImS8 DisableInputsFrames; // Disable window interactions for N frames
2130  ImGuiCond SetWindowPosAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowPos() use.
2131  ImGuiCond SetWindowSizeAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowSize() use.
2132  ImGuiCond SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowCollapsed() use.
2133  ImVec2 SetWindowPosVal; // store window position when using a non-zero Pivot (position set needs to be processed when we know the window size)
2134  ImVec2 SetWindowPosPivot; // store window pivot for positioning. ImVec2(0, 0) when positioning from top-left corner; ImVec2(0.5f, 0.5f) for centering; ImVec2(1, 1) for bottom right.
2135 
2136  ImVector<ImGuiID> IDStack; // ID stack. ID are hashes seeded with the value at the top of the stack. (In theory this should be in the TempData structure)
2137  ImGuiWindowTempData DC; // Temporary per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the "DC" variable name.
2138 
2139  // The best way to understand what those rectangles are is to use the 'Metrics->Tools->Show Windows Rectangles' viewer.
2140  // The main 'OuterRect', omitted as a field, is window->Rect().
2141  ImRect OuterRectClipped; // == Window->Rect() just after setup in Begin(). == window->Rect() for root window.
2142  ImRect InnerRect; // Inner rectangle (omit title bar, menu bar, scroll bar)
2143  ImRect InnerClipRect; // == InnerRect shrunk by WindowPadding*0.5f on each side, clipped within viewport or parent clip rect.
2144  ImRect WorkRect; // Initially covers the whole scrolling region. Reduced by containers e.g columns/tables when active. Shrunk by WindowPadding*1.0f on each side. This is meant to replace ContentRegionRect over time (from 1.71+ onward).
2145  ImRect ParentWorkRect; // Backup of WorkRect before entering a container such as columns/tables. Used by e.g. SpanAllColumns functions to easily access. Stacked containers are responsible for maintaining this. // FIXME-WORKRECT: Could be a stack?
2146  ImRect ClipRect; // Current clipping/scissoring rectangle, evolve as we are using PushClipRect(), etc. == DrawList->clip_rect_stack.back().
2147  ImRect ContentRegionRect; // FIXME: This is currently confusing/misleading. It is essentially WorkRect but not handling of scrolling. We currently rely on it as right/bottom aligned sizing operation need some size to rely on.
2148  ImVec2ih HitTestHoleSize; // Define an optional rectangular hole where mouse will pass-through the window.
2149  ImVec2ih HitTestHoleOffset;
2150

2152  float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp the window was Active (using float as we don't need high precision there)
2153  float ItemWidthDefault;

2155  ImVector<ImGuiOldColumns> ColumnsStorage;
2156  float FontWindowScale; // User scale multiplier per-window, via SetWindowFontScale()
2157  int SettingsOffset; // Offset into SettingsWindows[] (offsets are always valid as we only grow the array from the back)

2160  ImDrawList DrawListInst;

2162  ImGuiWindow* ParentWindowInBeginStack;
2163  ImGuiWindow* RootWindow; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Doesn't cross through popups/dock nodes.
2164  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowPopupTree; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Cross through popups parent<>child.
2165  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForTitleBarHighlight; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which will display TitleBgActive color when this window is active.
2166  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForNav; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which doesn't have the NavFlattened flag.

2173  int MemoryDrawListVtxCapacity;

2185  // We don't use g.FontSize because the window may be != g.CurrentWindow.
2186  ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
2187  float CalcFontSize() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; float scale = g.FontBaseSize * FontWindowScale; if (ParentWindow) scale *= ParentWindow->FontWindowScale; return scale; }
2188  float TitleBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? 0.0f : CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f; }
2189  ImRect TitleBarRect() const { return ImRect(Pos, ImVec2(Pos.x + SizeFull.x, Pos.y + TitleBarHeight())); }
2190  float MenuBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) ? DC.MenuBarOffset.y + CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f : 0.0f; }
2191  ImRect MenuBarRect() const { float y1 = Pos.y + TitleBarHeight(); return ImRect(Pos.x, y1, Pos.x + SizeFull.x, y1 + MenuBarHeight()); }

2289 // [Internal] sizeof() ~ 104
2290 // We use the terminology "Enabled" to refer to a column that is not Hidden by user/api.
2291 // We use the terminology "Clipped" to refer to a column that is out of sight because of scrolling/clipping.
2292 // This is in contrast with some user-facing api such as IsItemVisible() / IsRectVisible() which use "Visible" to mean "not clipped".

2297  float MinX; // Absolute positions
2298  float MaxX;
2299  float WidthRequest; // Master width absolute value when !(Flags & _WidthStretch). When Stretch this is derived every frame from StretchWeight in TableUpdateLayout()
2300  float WidthAuto; // Automatic width
2301  float StretchWeight; // Master width weight when (Flags & _WidthStretch). Often around ~1.0f initially.
2302  float InitStretchWeightOrWidth; // Value passed to TableSetupColumn(). For Width it is a content width (_without padding_).
2303  ImRect ClipRect; // Clipping rectangle for the column

2305  float WorkMinX; // Contents region min ~(MinX + CellPaddingX + CellSpacingX1) == cursor start position when entering column

2311  float ContentMaxXHeadersIdeal;
2312  ImS16 NameOffset; // Offset into parent ColumnsNames[]

2314  ImGuiTableColumnIdx IndexWithinEnabledSet; // Index within enabled/visible set (<= IndexToDisplayOrder)
2315  ImGuiTableColumnIdx PrevEnabledColumn; // Index of prev enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if first enabled/visible column
2316  ImGuiTableColumnIdx NextEnabledColumn; // Index of next enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if last enabled/visible column

2479 // Transient data that are only needed between BeginTable() and EndTable(), those buffers are shared (1 per level of stacked table).

2548  // We should always have a CurrentWindow in the stack (there is an implicit "Debug" window)
2549  // If this ever crash because g.CurrentWindow is NULL it means that either
2550  // - ImGui::NewFrame() has never been called, which is illegal.
2551  // - You are calling ImGui functions after ImGui::EndFrame()/ImGui::Render() and before the next ImGui::NewFrame(), which is also illegal.

2719  // FIXME: Eventually we should aim to move e.g. IsActiveIdUsingKey() into IsKeyXXX functions.
2720  inline bool IsNamedKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_NamedKey_END; }
2721  inline bool IsNamedKeyOrModKey(ImGuiKey key) { return (key >= ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_NamedKey_END) || key == ImGuiMod_Ctrl || key == ImGuiMod_Shift || key == ImGuiMod_Alt || key == ImGuiMod_Super; }
2722  inline bool IsLegacyKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_LegacyNativeKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_LegacyNativeKey_END; }
2723  inline bool IsGamepadKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Gamepad_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Gamepad_END; }
2724  inline bool IsAliasKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Aliases_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Aliases_END; }
2725  inline ImGuiKey ConvertSingleModFlagToKey(ImGuiKey key)
2726  {
2727  if (key == ImGuiMod_Ctrl) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModCtrl;
2728  if (key == ImGuiMod_Shift) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModShift;
2729  if (key == ImGuiMod_Alt) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModAlt;
2730  if (key == ImGuiMod_Super) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModSuper;
2731  return key;
2732  }

2961  // Refactored focus/nav/tabbing system in 1.82 and 1.84. If you have old/custom copy-and-pasted widgets that used FocusableItemRegister():
2962  // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM < 18209: using 'ItemAdd(....)' and 'bool tab_focused = FocusableItemRegister(...)'
2963  // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18209: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Focused) != 0'
2964  // (New) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18413: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_FocusedTabbing) != 0 || g.NavActivateInputId == id' (WIP)
2965  // Widget code are simplified as there's no need to call FocusableItemUnregister() while managing the transition from regular widget to TempInputText()
2966  inline bool FocusableItemRegister(ImGuiWindow* window, ImGuiID id) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); IM_UNUSED(id); return false; } // -> pass ImGuiItemAddFlags_Inputable flag to ItemAdd()
2967  inline void FocusableItemUnregister(ImGuiWindow* window) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); } // -> unnecessary: TempInputText() uses ImGuiInputTextFlags_MergedItem
2968 #endif
